commit.message: Add PrettyVal instance for Data.Fixed
Bump version

Merge together a literal followed immediately by some hex-digits into a single token.

This fixes #35, although technically it does not follow
Haskell's lexical syntax.
Avoid warnings

If a constructor is applied to more values, add them as children.

This could happen if the input had extra parens.  See issue #34.
Allow varsyms to be used as infix constructors.
Allow keywords as the names of constructors
Don't do "cabal check"
Update travis to build with more recent GHC
Add hiding support to the executable.
Fix typo in comment.
Export `hideCon`
Fix warnings.

A more conveninet way to do pre-processing.

This requires parsing the value twice, but hopefully that's not too much
of a bottle neck.
